<subSubSection id="C30F653F5DCFFF14FF63BE9737B1825E" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="8BAA36B45DCFFF14FF63BE973754834E" blockId="137.[189,1399,502,768]" box="[189,303,502,528]" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">
<emphasis id="B961EAA65DCFFF14FF63BE973754834E" bold="true" box="[189,303,502,528]" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Remarks</emphasis>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BAA36B45DCFFF14FF63BD4637B1825E" blockId="137.[189,1399,502,768]" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">
The new species can be readily distinguished from other species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D375DCFFF14FC36BD463240831F" authorityName="Loew" authorityYear="1859" box="[1000,1083,551,577]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Stilpon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B961EAA65DCFFF14FC36BD463240831F" box="[1000,1083,551,577]" italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Stilpon</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
described from 
<collectingCountry id="F30276245DCFFF14FADEBD46330C831F" box="[1280,1399,551,577]" name="Singapore" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Singapore</collectingCountry>
and from the Oriental Region because 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D375DCFFF14FD4CBD2F35438339" authority="Grootaert &amp; Shamshev, 2012" authorityName="Grootaert &amp; Shamshev" authorityYear="2012" box="[658,824,590,616]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Stilpon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripennis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B961EAA65DCFFF14FD4CBD2F35438339" box="[658,824,590,616]" italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">S. nigripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25257DD5DCFFF14FC9FBD2F35E48336" box="[833,927,590,616]" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
is the only species lacking R 
<subScript id="179134F15DCFFF14FADABD3E33648333" attach="left" box="[1284,1311,607,621]" fontSize="6" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">2+3</subScript>
. In the Palaearctic Region an abbreviated vein R 
<subScript id="179134F15DCFFF14FD72BDE434BC83CD" attach="left" box="[684,711,645,659]" fontSize="6" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">2+3</subScript>
is present in 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D375DCFFF14FCB2BD1532DF83D0" authority="(Perris, 1852)" baseAuthorityName="Perris" baseAuthorityYear="1852" box="[876,1188,627,654]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Tachydromia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="paludosa">
<emphasis id="B961EAA65DCFFF14FCB2BD15358C83D3" box="[876,1015,627,654]" italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">S. paludosa</emphasis>
(Perris, 1852)
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D375DCFFF14FB3FBD15372583EA" authority="(Seguy, 1950)" baseAuthorityName="Seguy" baseAuthorityYear="1950" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Stilpon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="delamarei">
<emphasis id="B961EAA65DCFFF14FB3FBD15330C83D3" box="[1249,1399,627,654]" italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">S. delamarei</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF844B455DCFFF14FF1BBDF8372D83EA" author="Seguy" box="[197,342,665,692]" firstAuthor="Seguy" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" pagination="83 - 87" refId="ref70338" refString="Seguy E. 1950. Un nouveau genre de Corynetine du Midi de la France (Dipt., Empididae). Vie et milieu 1: 83 - 87." type="journal article" year="1950">Séguy, 1950</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
both known from the Pyrenees and an unnamed species taken from 
<collectingCountry id="F30276245DCFFF14FBBEBDF832A883ED" box="[1120,1235,665,691]" name="Tajikistan" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">Tajikistan</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation id="EF844B455DCFFF14FB3EBDF837FF8384" author="Shamshev I. V. &amp; Grootaert P." firstAuthor="Shamshev" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" pagination="81 - 86" refId="ref70594" refString="Shamshev I. V. &amp; Grootaert P. 2005 d. New data on the genus Stilpon Loew (Diptera: Hybotidae) from the Palaearctic region, with description of a new species from Tajikistan. Belgian Journal of Entomology 7: 81 - 86." type="journal article" year="2005" yearSuffix="d">Shamshev &amp; Grootaert 2005d</bibRefCitation>
). The relationships of 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D375DCFFF14FD4EBDA1354F8387" authority="Grootaert &amp; Shamshev, 2012" authorityName="Grootaert &amp; Shamshev" authorityYear="2012" box="[656,820,704,730]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Stilpon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigripennis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B961EAA65DCFFF14FD4EBDA1354F8387" box="[656,820,704,730]" italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">S. nigripennis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A25257DD5DCFFF14FCE3BDA135E28384" box="[829,921,704,730]" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
are unresolved beyond inclusion within the 
<taxonomicName id="4C154D375DCFFF14FF36BD87370C83A1" authorityName="Smith" authorityYear="1965" box="[232,375,741,768]" class="Insecta" family="Hybotidae" genus="Stilpon" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="137" pageNumber="138" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="divergens">
<emphasis id="B961EAA65DCFFF14FF36BD87370C83A1" box="[232,375,741,768]" italics="true" pageId="137" pageNumber="138">S. divergens</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group.
</paragraph>
